Now whatwas he going to do?

744
01:01:08.296 --> 01:01:10.088
Middle of the day.

745
01:01:12.258 --> 01:01:14.676
He goes to work, telIs the boss:

746
01:01:14.886 --> 01:01:18.138
"Give me 50 thousand".
"What, are you nuts?"


747
01:01:18.306 --> 01:01:22.893
"Nuts, eh? Just you wait."
He goes home. Gets a shotgun, shells.


748
01:01:23.060 --> 01:01:26.646
And goes back. By this time
the boss had run off some place.


749
01:01:26.814 --> 01:01:30.192
He goes to the accounting office.
There are onlywomen there.


750
01:01:30.318 --> 01:01:33.904
He takes three of them hostage.

751
01:01:34.071 --> 01:01:36.865
He becomes a terrorist.

752
01:01:38.576 --> 01:01:41.953
He makes them put
a bucket outside with a note,


753
01:01:42.121 --> 01:01:45.874
his demands -
all 57 thousand rubles,


754
01:01:47.001 --> 01:01:51.421
a luxury apartment,
ajob as chief engineer,


755
01:01:51.839 --> 01:01:55.300
and a plane to anywhere on earth
he chooses.


756
01:01:55.468 --> 01:01:58.094
Now, why did he askfor ajob,

757
01:01:58.679 --> 01:02:01.932
when he planned to
fly off in a plane?

758
01:02:02.099 --> 01:02:04.893
That's not important.
It's not important.


759
01:02:06.187 --> 01:02:09.940
The women say: "Uncle Kolya,
what are you doing? Look..."


760
01:02:10.441 --> 01:02:13.193
But hejust goes "oooo!"
He can't speak.


761
01:02:13.402 --> 01:02:18.031
The women open the safe
and take out 800 rubles.


762
01:02:18.199 --> 01:02:21.243
One goes to buy vodka,
a half case, ice cream.


763
01:02:21.410 --> 01:02:23.995
And the police are there, snipers.

764
01:02:24.205 --> 01:02:26.873
"He's a terrorist! Get him! Fire!"

765
01:02:27.083 --> 01:02:31.837
But the police chief says:
"Stop! Absolutely not! Don't shoot!


766
01:02:32.004 --> 01:02:34.172
I'll go myself!"
What a man!


767
01:02:34.382 --> 01:02:37.175
And he goes in unarmed. What a man!

768
01:02:37.385 --> 01:02:40.053
Uncle Kolya points the gun at him:
"I'll kill you".


769
01:02:40.263 --> 01:02:42.264
And the chief says: "No you won't".

770
01:02:42.473 --> 01:02:47.435
"Why not?"
"Because I'm the chief", says the chief.


771
01:02:47.562 --> 01:02:50.689
Uncle Kolya drops the shotgun.

772
01:02:51.607 --> 01:02:55.277
They sit around the case ofvodka.

773
01:02:56.112 --> 01:02:58.029
They have a drink.

774
01:02:58.281 --> 01:03:00.156
And cry.

775
01:03:01.158 --> 01:03:04.578
And there was no trial, no investigation.

776
01:03:19.760 --> 01:03:24.222
l beg your pardon, butwhy exactly
did you tell us all that?


777
01:03:24.390 --> 01:03:29.311
Why? He could have been sent to prison,

778
01:03:29.478 --> 01:03:31.605
or shot. A terrorist!

779
01:03:31.856 --> 01:03:35.775
But the police chief, what a man.
What a man! Nothing.


780
01:03:35.943 --> 01:03:40.572
Uncle Kolya worked and paid off his debt.
l helped a bit.


781
01:03:40.698 --> 01:03:44.242
The police chief moved up.
He became a businessman.


782
01:03:44.452 --> 01:03:47.704
And "Brother" was burned down.

783
01:03:47.914 --> 01:03:50.248
But by someone else,
not Uncle Kolya.


784
01:03:50.458 --> 01:03:52.876
That's wonderful.

785
01:03:53.210 --> 01:03:58.048
Butwhat does all that have to do
with this case?


786
01:03:59.050 --> 01:04:00.800
lf... if...

787
01:04:02.970 --> 01:04:04.763
I'm for kindness.

788
01:04:05.306 --> 01:04:08.266
Your brains sure curdled fast, brother.

789
01:04:08.517 --> 01:04:12.187
No, no.
l don't have cottage cheese up here!


790
01:04:12.355 --> 01:04:15.774
A good man should be helped.

791
01:04:15.900 --> 01:04:17.901
And a bad man should be...

792
01:04:21.197 --> 01:04:24.324
l vote that the young Chechen
is not guilty.


793
01:04:24.492 --> 01:04:26.242
Write it down. Thankyou.

794
01:04:27.536 --> 01:04:28.912
Well!

795
01:04:29.705 --> 01:04:31.706
That's amazing!

796
01:04:32.166 --> 01:04:35.418
What kind ofjustice is that?

797
01:04:35.878 --> 01:04:38.880
Uncle Kolya the plumber
runs around drunk.


798
01:04:39.090 --> 01:04:42.634
Uncle Lyosha the police chief
drinks vodka with him.


799
01:04:42.760 --> 01:04:46.888
Uncle Vasya the city prosecutor
turns a blind eye.


800
01:04:47.014 --> 01:04:49.766
And the criminal remains at large!

801
01:04:51.978 --> 01:04:55.105
And meanwhile the entire
civilized world


802
01:04:55.272 --> 01:04:59.109
has lived for centuries
according to the law.


803
01:05:02.488 --> 01:05:05.532
A Russian man will
never live by the law.


804
01:05:05.700 --> 01:05:09.285
- Why not?
- The law bores him.


805
01:05:10.913 --> 01:05:12.914
The law is dead.

806
01:05:13.082 --> 01:05:15.667
There's nothing personal about it.

807
01:05:15.876 --> 01:05:20.046
And a Russian man without that
personal touch is an empty shell.


808
01:05:20.214 --> 01:05:22.090
He won't steal or guard.

809
01:05:22.383 --> 01:05:24.467
But that's awful!

810
01:05:24.635 --> 01:05:26.803
Who said itwas good?

811
01:05:26.971 --> 01:05:29.305
Look at that horrible pipe.

812
01:05:30.266 --> 01:05:32.100
It's obscene.

813
01:05:32.268 --> 01:05:34.811
Total filth in the center of Moscow.

814
01:05:35.062 --> 01:05:37.772
ln a school,
where they teach children.


815
01:05:38.024 --> 01:05:41.359
The builders forgot to run
a proper heating pipe,


816
01:05:41.569 --> 01:05:44.029
and then the school was built.

817
01:05:44.280 --> 01:05:47.615
They should cut offtheir limbs
and put them in prison.


818
01:05:47.742 --> 01:05:49.117
By law.

819
01:05:49.326 --> 01:05:54.080
But there are personal ties.
Human ones. Russian ones.


820
01:05:54.248 --> 01:05:59.377
The school let them temporarily
hang that thing. Temporarily.


821
01:05:59.545 --> 01:06:04.674
And it has a corrosive effect
on the minds of the children.


822
01:06:04.842 --> 01:06:08.136
Maybe that's why they leave
their bras in the bathroom.


823
01:06:08.345 --> 01:06:10.764
And nobody gets steamed up.

824
01:06:10.931 --> 01:06:13.475
What's the law got to do with it?

825
01:06:14.351 --> 01:06:16.311
Human relations.

826
01:06:18.064 --> 01:06:20.482
Here! You'll love this.

827
01:06:24.945 --> 01:06:28.615
lnventory number 72-17-99.

828
01:06:28.824 --> 01:06:31.117
Young Eagle Pioneer Camp.

829
01:06:31.285 --> 01:06:33.787
1967.

830
01:06:34.246 --> 01:06:36.164
l wasn't even born then.

831
01:06:37.541 --> 01:06:39.793
Do you see how it is?

832
01:06:40.294 --> 01:06:42.670
40 years have passed. 40 years!

833
01:06:42.838 --> 01:06:45.256
And we still can'twake up
from the coma.


834
01:06:46.550 --> 01:06:49.928
4 decades of running in place.

835
01:06:53.182 --> 01:06:57.227
That's it. I missed my train.
The troupe leftwithout me.


836
01:06:57.520 --> 01:07:00.355
But I'm here. And I'm voting.

837
01:07:01.357 --> 01:07:04.692
The young Chechen is not guilty.

838
01:07:05.945 --> 01:07:07.695
Write it down. Period.

839
01:07:08.447 --> 01:07:09.948
Shit...

840
01:07:10.116 --> 01:07:12.951
What are you...? Aw, hell!
What did... See what you did?


841
01:07:13.494 --> 01:07:17.997
- This is a circus?
- Actually, I'lljoin them! Write that, too!


842
01:07:18.124 --> 01:07:20.458
Let's alljoin them!

843
01:07:20.960 --> 01:07:24.838
- Wonderful...
- I also think the kid's not guilty!


844
01:07:26.382 --> 01:07:31.386
And, incidentally,
l have reasonable doubts.


845
01:07:31.846 --> 01:07:35.890
Can you explain why

846
01:07:36.016 --> 01:07:39.144
if he killed and robbed
his adoptive father...


847
01:07:40.271 --> 01:07:44.649
...he returned with the money
to the scene of the crime?


848
01:07:44.775 --> 01:07:46.192
Yes, good point.

849
01:07:47.403 --> 01:07:50.155
Atypical murdererwouldn't do that.

850
01:07:50.447 --> 01:07:52.866
Listen, just listen.

851
01:07:53.117 --> 01:07:56.578
OK, you're a respectable man,
a college dean.


852
01:07:56.704 --> 01:08:00.832
How can you say that?
What does "typical murderer" mean?


853
01:08:01.041 --> 01:08:03.293
Atypical one wouldn't go back,
but this one did,


854
01:08:03.836 --> 01:08:06.963
because he's a stupid,
uneducated savage


855
01:08:07.214 --> 01:08:09.465
whojustjumped out of the tree.

856
01:08:09.800 --> 01:08:12.844
You expect him to write novels?

857
01:08:13.012 --> 01:08:16.723
You know perfectlywell,
those animaIs have tiny little bird brains.


858
01:08:16.932 --> 01:08:18.141
My dear sir...

859
01:08:18.350 --> 01:08:22.103
...excuse me, butjustwho
are you calling a savage?


860
01:08:22.229 --> 01:08:24.397
I'm also from the Caucasus,
for example.


861
01:08:24.565 --> 01:08:27.692
So the poet Rustaveli was a savage?

862
01:08:27.902 --> 01:08:31.821
The artist Pirosmani?
Directors like Paradzhanov?


863
01:08:31.989 --> 01:08:34.908
- Who's a savage?
- I don't mean them.


864
01:08:35.117 --> 01:08:39.037
I'm talking about the monster
who killed his father.


865
01:08:39.205 --> 01:08:41.706
I'm talking about myself.

866
01:08:41.874 --> 01:08:45.001
I'm also from the Caucasus.
l studied in Moscow.


867
01:08:45.169 --> 01:08:49.214
But I get called "monkey".
I'm no monkey, I'm a surgeon.


868
01:08:49.340 --> 01:08:53.218
A physician. I have my own clinic.
Understand?


869
01:08:53.344 --> 01:08:57.722
l don't doubt it, OK, so you're not
toiling away at county hospital.


870
01:08:57.932 --> 01:09:02.602
Then why do people come here
from the Caucasus to buy a diploma?


871
01:09:03.354 --> 01:09:05.230
What? To buywhat?

872
01:09:05.439 --> 01:09:08.191
- I bought one?
- I don't mean you.


873
01:09:08.359 --> 01:09:11.736
I'm asking you, wait!
l bought my diploma, yes?


874
01:09:12.655 --> 01:09:16.741
l never paid anyone
to getwhere I am!


875
01:09:16.909 --> 01:09:20.161
How dare you?
What gives you the right, huh?


876
01:09:20.287 --> 01:09:24.499
l tried 4 times before I got into
Moscow Medical School!


877
01:09:24.708 --> 01:09:30.463
And for all 4 years I worked
as an orderly at city hospital! Yes!


878
01:09:30.631 --> 01:09:36.010
l worked as a paramedic and in the ER.
l graduated in honor! "With honors" I mean.


879
01:09:36.178 --> 01:09:39.681
Yes,
so I don't speak Russian thatwell.


880
01:09:39.848 --> 01:09:43.101
So what?
Yes, I said "lun-icrous" by mistake.


881
01:09:43.477 --> 01:09:46.980
So what? I apologized.
I'm still a good doctor!


882
01:09:47.147 --> 01:09:50.191
l don't doubt that you're a good doctor.
But I don't understand why


883
01:09:50.442 --> 01:09:53.444
a good doctor like you
would vote guilty


884
01:09:53.570 --> 01:09:57.532
if everyone in the Caucasus
is so cultured...


885
01:09:57.658 --> 01:09:59.993
That's why I voted guilty.

886
01:10:00.160 --> 01:10:03.871
It's an unheard of affront
in the Caucasus


887
01:10:04.081 --> 01:10:06.499
to raise a hand against an elder.

888
01:10:06.667 --> 01:10:09.794
Especially if he tookyou
into his home, his family.


889
01:10:10.754 --> 01:10:12.171
Brothers, brothers...

890
01:10:13.465 --> 01:10:15.383
Gentlemen... Comrades...

891
01:10:15.801 --> 01:10:18.720
Come on, let's be civilized.
For God's sake.


892
01:10:18.846 --> 01:10:21.806
I'm over here writing, plus one,
not guilty, guilty...


893
01:10:22.057 --> 01:10:24.309
...let's be civilized, let's do it again.

894
01:10:24.518 --> 01:10:28.521
Let's all vote calmly.
We'll write everything down so it's clear.


895
01:10:28.772 --> 01:10:32.191
- So let's vote, OK?
- Can we vote by show of hands?


896
01:10:32.318 --> 01:10:34.235
Now. Who votes

897
01:10:34.486 --> 01:10:39.115
to find the accused not guilty?

898
01:10:40.242 --> 01:10:44.787
Not guilty. Please pay attention.
Not guilty.


899
01:10:44.997 --> 01:10:46.372
One,

900
01:10:46.582 --> 01:10:50.251
two, three, four,

901
01:10:50.753 --> 01:10:52.003
five.

902
01:10:52.463 --> 01:10:56.090
Who votes to find the defendant guilty?

903
01:10:57.176 --> 01:11:00.762
One, two, three, four, five,

904
01:11:00.888 --> 01:11:02.388
six...

905
01:11:03.682 --> 01:11:04.891
Seven.

906
01:11:05.059 --> 01:11:06.809
Seven "for"...

907
01:11:07.144 --> 01:11:10.438
Five for "not guilty",
seven for "guilty".


908
01:13:17.483 --> 01:13:22.069
The boundary is here, right?
So it's a mirror image.


909
01:13:22.196 --> 01:13:24.113
Let's reproduce it.

910
01:13:24.281 --> 01:13:29.744
So your amateurtheatre is going to
recreate the crime scene exactly?


911
01:13:29.828 --> 01:13:34.040
Exactly? No, how could we?
One apartmentwas on top of the other.


912
01:13:34.249 --> 01:13:38.920
We'll try to mirror-image them,
according to this floor plan.


913
01:13:39.129 --> 01:13:43.799
Listen, the old man downstairs heard
the boy shout "I'll kill you".


914
01:13:44.009 --> 01:13:48.054
And a falling body
and he sawthe boy run away, right?


915
01:13:48.597 --> 01:13:53.434
Have any of you been
to the scene of the murder?


916
01:13:53.644 --> 01:13:54.936
Of course not.

917
01:13:55.145 --> 01:13:59.440
You know, I have...
l went afterthe first day of the trial...


918
01:13:59.566 --> 01:14:01.359
because I was curious to see

919
01:14:01.985 --> 01:14:06.197
a building where only two apartments
were occupied.


920
01:14:06.406 --> 01:14:10.535
ln one, a murder, in the other,
a witness to the murder.


921
01:14:10.744 --> 01:14:12.161
And nobody else.

922
01:14:12.412 --> 01:14:15.665
What's that got to do
with this case?


923
01:14:15.791 --> 01:14:19.585
Next to the building
there's a construction site.


924
01:14:19.795 --> 01:14:23.839
They're building luxury apartments.
There's lots of machinery.


925
01:14:23.966 --> 01:14:28.010
- Theywork around the clock.
- Around the clock. So what?


926
01:14:28.136 --> 01:14:32.890
lmagine the noise
of a building site outside yourwindow.


927
01:14:33.100 --> 01:14:34.392
Your point?

928
01:14:34.643 --> 01:14:37.937
The old man claims he heard
the boy shout "I'll kill you"


929
01:14:38.146 --> 01:14:43.693
and then he heard something fall,
and he says he recognized the boy's voice.


930
01:14:43.860 --> 01:14:45.444
Yeah, so? What? What?

931
01:14:45.946 --> 01:14:51.242
With all due respect to the witness,
l don't believe him.


932
01:14:51.410 --> 01:14:54.453
Wait. One second.
So you're telling us


933
01:14:54.663 --> 01:14:58.666
that the old man knowingly lied in court,
under oath?


934
01:14:58.834 --> 01:15:01.002
An old-school communist

935
01:15:01.253 --> 01:15:05.214
slandered an innocent Chechen boy
for no reason?


936
01:15:05.340 --> 01:15:09.969
lf anyone lied, under oath and otherwise,
itwas the communists.


937
01:15:10.178 --> 01:15:14.223
They lied from top to bottom,
every one of them.


938
01:15:14.391 --> 01:15:18.144
For privileges, for power,
and just out of habit.


939
01:15:18.353 --> 01:15:21.897
Let's not talk about that, please.

940
01:15:22.107 --> 01:15:24.191
Some people were different.

941
01:15:24.359 --> 01:15:27.486
Myfatherwas a regional party secretary
in the Urals.


942
01:15:27.654 --> 01:15:30.698
Privileges? What privileges?

943
01:15:30.949 --> 01:15:35.369
Sometimes we didn't see him foryears.
His heartwas shot at 50.


944
01:15:35.495 --> 01:15:38.914
After he retired,
he burned outwithin 3 months.


945
01:15:39.124 --> 01:15:42.918
They spit him out like old gum.
Privileges, you say?


946
01:15:43.128 --> 01:15:45.838
How do you think it looks?

947
01:15:46.715 --> 01:15:48.758
- Pretty close.
- Pretty close.


948
01:15:49.217 --> 01:15:53.596
Now, we've created two identical
apartments in mirror image.


949
01:15:53.722 --> 01:15:57.767
As I said, one's on top of the other,
so they're identical.


950
01:15:58.143 --> 01:16:01.020
ln his testimony the old man said

951
01:16:01.396 --> 01:16:04.899
that at the time of the crime
he was lying...


952
01:16:05.734 --> 01:16:09.487
...on the living room sofa...
No, I can't see anything.


953
01:16:09.738 --> 01:16:11.697
I'll ask the bailiff.

954
01:16:18.497 --> 01:16:19.955
What's that?

955
01:16:20.165 --> 01:16:23.292
The train. I'll call you back.

956
01:16:31.510 --> 01:16:32.843
Oh Lord!

957
01:16:37.265 --> 01:16:40.309
- You rang?
- Can you turn on the light?


958
01:16:40.560 --> 01:16:43.104
We need to read. 
It's an experiment.

959
01:16:43.355 --> 01:16:45.272
It's nighttime.

960
01:16:47.150 --> 01:16:49.860
All right, I'll turn it on.

961
01:16:59.579 --> 01:17:01.747
You'll have light.

962
01:17:03.417 --> 01:17:05.251
Yeltsin's fault.

963
01:17:08.213 --> 01:17:09.630
Thankyou.

964
01:17:09.923 --> 01:17:11.132
Thankyou, Boris.

965
01:17:11.425 --> 01:17:14.260
The old man was lying right here
on the sofa.


966
01:17:14.469 --> 01:17:16.470
The crime happened here.

967
01:17:16.722 --> 01:17:21.100
He said his living room is
underthe room where the murderwas.


968
01:17:21.309 --> 01:17:25.271
Did anyone notice howthe old man
walked to the stand?


969
01:17:25.397 --> 01:17:29.608
Yes, I rememberverywell!
He walked slowly, his knees didn't bend.


970
01:17:29.735 --> 01:17:31.569
Because he has arthritis.

971
01:17:31.987 --> 01:17:35.531
The floor plan shows
all the room dimensions.


972
01:17:35.741 --> 01:17:41.287
And we've reproduced them almost exactly,

973
01:17:41.371 --> 01:17:43.456
to see he had to
get up from the sofa,

974
01:17:43.999 --> 01:17:47.960
walk 35 meters, open the door,

975
01:17:48.253 --> 01:17:50.671
and still manage to see someone.

976
01:17:50.881 --> 01:17:55.426
- Anyone know average walking speed?
- A meter and a half per second.


977
01:17:55.635 --> 01:17:58.429
- A meter and a half.
- lf you're healthy.


978
01:17:58.597 --> 01:18:01.307
So, 10 seconds is 15 meters.

979
01:18:01.558 --> 01:18:03.267
So 35 meters is about 25 seconds.

980
01:18:03.477 --> 01:18:08.397
And we'll see which one of us
gets to the doorfirst.


