What scheme?

1483
01:55:48.781 --> 01:55:52.242
When the big fish don't
give a thought to the little people,


1484
01:55:53.161 --> 01:55:57.080
who have to get by
howeverthey can.


1485
01:55:57.498 --> 01:55:59.249
By their own rules.

1486
01:56:00.168 --> 01:56:01.668
It's like that everywhere.

1487
01:56:01.961 --> 01:56:04.463
ln construction, in hospitals,

1488
01:56:04.756 --> 01:56:06.214
and in cemeteries.

1489
01:56:06.424 --> 01:56:08.884
What do cemeteries
have to do with it?


1490
01:56:10.303 --> 01:56:12.554
Have you ever buried anyone?

1491
01:56:13.222 --> 01:56:14.556
Me?

1492
01:56:15.975 --> 01:56:17.601
Yes, I have.

1493
01:56:20.605 --> 01:56:24.232
Two years ago.
ln London. Matilda.


1494
01:56:24.400 --> 01:56:25.734
Who was she?

1495
01:56:28.154 --> 01:56:29.863
A Rottweiler.

1496
01:56:30.406 --> 01:56:33.450
That's not a name.
It's a breed of dog.


1497
01:56:34.202 --> 01:56:37.162
l don't know howthey bury dogs
in London,


1498
01:56:37.330 --> 01:56:40.791
but I do know how we see people off
on theirfinaljourney.


1499
01:56:40.958 --> 01:56:45.712
I've been a cemetery directorfor 8 years.
Now, imagine this.


1500
01:56:45.797 --> 01:56:50.258
You're burying a loved one.
Afuneral service, the usual.


1501
01:56:50.384 --> 01:56:52.427
You go to the graveyard.

1502
01:56:52.637 --> 01:56:55.347
- Like this.
- What are you...? What grave?


1503
01:56:55.556 --> 01:56:57.307
- That's mom.
- Sorry.


1504
01:56:57.517 --> 01:56:59.392
My mom's there.

1505
01:56:59.602 --> 01:57:02.062
- Well, it's...
- My mom.


1506
01:57:02.772 --> 01:57:05.398
The final farewell, relatives.

1507
01:57:05.608 --> 01:57:08.985
And some old lady standing nearby.

1508
01:57:09.153 --> 01:57:11.988
She looks into the grave
and says "Oh God, that poor man".


1509
01:57:12.198 --> 01:57:16.076
They say "What is it?"
They look, the grave's flooded.


1510
01:57:16.452 --> 01:57:17.994
How can that be?

1511
01:57:18.162 --> 01:57:22.541
What can they do? You can't
put your loved one in a swamp.


1512
01:57:22.834 --> 01:57:25.043
And the old grannywhispers advice.

1513
01:57:25.545 --> 01:57:29.297
They go to the head gravedigger,
who's there.


1514
01:57:30.049 --> 01:57:33.927
They say: "Sir, there's water in there.
Please do something".


1515
01:57:34.470 --> 01:57:38.306
He gives them some line
about ground water


1516
01:57:38.432 --> 01:57:41.017
and he shoveIs the liquid
out of the grave.


1517
01:57:41.185 --> 01:57:43.728
But it runs back in. 
They're in shock.

1518
01:57:43.896 --> 01:57:48.942
The old lady tugs at someone's sleeve
and shows them another grave nearby,


1519
01:57:49.318 --> 01:57:51.736
that's completely dry.

1520
01:57:51.946 --> 01:57:53.488
And pristine.

1521
01:57:53.865 --> 01:57:56.366
Now here's the interesting part.

1522
01:57:56.659 --> 01:57:59.786
The relatives ask the digger,

1523
01:57:59.954 --> 01:58:03.290
"Listen is there anyway
we can change places?"


1524
01:58:03.708 --> 01:58:05.333
"Are you crazy?"

1525
01:58:06.085 --> 01:58:09.462
They're burying someone there
in 15 minutes.


1526
01:58:09.589 --> 01:58:12.299
No way. All the paperwork's done"

1527
01:58:12.800 --> 01:58:18.513
They get on their knees, in tears;,
"Sir, please help us. We'll pay.


1528
01:58:18.598 --> 01:58:20.307
Just tell us how much".

1529
01:58:20.516 --> 01:58:23.935
The rest is easy.
He looks at their clothes.


1530
01:58:24.061 --> 01:58:26.646
for you, 2000 bucks.

1531
01:58:27.398 --> 01:58:31.651
For someone else, 500. lfthey're poor
he won't even look at them.


1532
01:58:32.653 --> 01:58:37.282
They swap stones.
The dead guy gets a dry grave


1533
01:58:37.408 --> 01:58:41.578
The family leaves.
The old lady gets 500 rubles


1534
01:58:42.121 --> 01:58:45.957
They pull out the plastic sheetfrom
underthe grave


1535
01:58:46.375 --> 01:58:49.085
and in 15 minutes it's dry.

1536
01:58:50.379 --> 01:58:54.633
And the diggers are ready
to rig up anotherwet grave.


1537
01:58:55.885 --> 01:58:57.802
That's it.

1538
01:59:08.773 --> 01:59:11.983
I'm glad we cremated
my mother in law.


1539
01:59:16.447 --> 01:59:18.698
Very interesting.

1540
01:59:24.538 --> 01:59:27.499
Why are you looking at me?

1541
01:59:29.752 --> 01:59:32.671
Is it differentwhere you work?

1542
01:59:35.258 --> 01:59:38.218
Everyone's in on it. Everyone.

1543
01:59:38.844 --> 01:59:41.137
ln their own way.

1544
01:59:41.555 --> 01:59:43.014
Right, friend?

1545
01:59:46.727 --> 01:59:48.270
Rolex?

1546
01:59:48.688 --> 01:59:50.272
Yeah.

1547
01:59:50.940 --> 01:59:52.691
Expensive.

1548
01:59:55.069 --> 01:59:56.069
Well, yeah.

1549
01:59:56.279 --> 01:59:58.071
On your cemetery pay?

1550
02:00:01.200 --> 02:00:02.617
Yes...

1551
02:00:04.453 --> 02:00:07.747
...on my cemetery pay. I won't lie

1552
02:00:09.083 --> 02:00:11.876
But I also used that cemetery pay

1553
02:00:12.044 --> 02:00:14.629
to restore the chapel.

1554
02:00:14.797 --> 02:00:18.508
And I feed the bums who
hang around the cemetery.


1555
02:00:18.634 --> 02:00:21.177
They have to eat somewhere.

1556
02:00:22.054 --> 02:00:26.641
And I built a school in the town
where I was born, 830 km from Moscow.


1557
02:00:28.686 --> 02:00:31.354
lt has a gym... come visit,
you'll see.


1558
02:00:31.522 --> 02:00:35.191
And we don't have monstrosities,
like that pipe.


1559
02:00:35.318 --> 02:00:38.236
My pipes are underground,
where they should be.


1560
02:00:38.404 --> 02:00:43.033
There's a computer lab with
LCD screens.


1561
02:00:43.200 --> 02:00:47.203
Local teachers, all with
good salaries.


1562
02:00:48.331 --> 02:00:51.666
We have a bus to bring kids
from farther away.


1563
02:00:51.792 --> 02:00:54.002
And take them home, of course.

1564
02:00:54.170 --> 02:00:57.422
So they don't have time
to sniff glue.


1565
02:00:59.342 --> 02:01:02.969
And if you ask
the people in the village:


1566
02:01:03.763 --> 02:01:08.058
"Where'd the money to build this
school come from?"


1567
02:01:11.062 --> 02:01:15.565
They couldn't care less where
the money came from,


1568
02:01:16.609 --> 02:01:19.652
as long as the school stays
up and running.


1569
02:01:19.779 --> 02:01:23.698
So I use moneyfrom the dead
to help the living.


1570
02:01:24.158 --> 02:01:26.826
Since nobody else is going to.

1571
02:01:36.128 --> 02:01:39.172
ln short, the Chechen is not guilty.

1572
02:01:41.967 --> 02:01:44.302
Still, can you explain to me,

1573
02:01:44.470 --> 02:01:48.932
an almost sane person,
why that simple woman,


1574
02:01:49.058 --> 02:01:51.017
who is not part of any scheme,

1575
02:01:51.185 --> 02:01:54.229
testified in court
that the Chechen


1576
02:01:54.355 --> 02:01:57.148
killed the Russian officer
Volodya with a knife?


1577
02:01:57.358 --> 02:01:59.401
l know why.

1578
02:02:00.027 --> 02:02:03.947
You can yell at me.
You can laugh. But I know.


1579
02:02:04.323 --> 02:02:07.033
- ltwasjealousy.
- What?


1580
02:02:09.203 --> 02:02:11.204
Jealousy,

1581
02:02:11.747 --> 02:02:15.708
She didn't hearthe boy,
she lives across the street.


1582
02:02:15.835 --> 02:02:19.963
She didn't see anything either
because itwas night time.


1583
02:02:20.089 --> 02:02:24.342
At best, she saw some shadows,
though I doubt it.


1584
02:02:24.468 --> 02:02:26.261
She didn't see anything.

1585
02:02:26.429 --> 02:02:29.472
She was convinced that itwas the boy
and no one else,


1586
02:02:29.640 --> 02:02:32.559
because she wanted
and was prepared to see


1587
02:02:32.726 --> 02:02:35.770
the worst in him.

1588
02:02:35.896 --> 02:02:37.313
Why?

1589
02:02:38.816 --> 02:02:40.316
Jealousy.

1590
02:02:40.484 --> 02:02:42.068
Terrible,

1591
02:02:42.486 --> 02:02:44.237
senseless, femalejealousy.

1592
02:02:44.780 --> 02:02:46.364
Look at these photos.

1593
02:02:46.574 --> 02:02:48.867
She showed them in court.

1594
02:02:49.952 --> 02:02:52.996
To prove that she knewthe victim.

1595
02:02:53.622 --> 02:02:56.458
Here's a photo of them at a party.

1596
02:02:56.625 --> 02:02:58.877
Her, the deceased, and his wife.

1597
02:02:59.044 --> 02:03:00.753
Now here's one...

1598
02:03:03.340 --> 02:03:06.384
...of her, him, and someone's arm.

1599
02:03:06.635 --> 02:03:08.636
It's his wife's arm.

1600
02:03:08.888 --> 02:03:13.141
Why did she need to go
and crop the photo


1601
02:03:13.267 --> 02:03:15.226
so it only shows her
and the deceased?


1602
02:03:15.519 --> 02:03:17.729
Cutting out the wife.

1603
02:03:19.106 --> 02:03:21.983
This is a photo of her dream.

1604
02:03:22.318 --> 02:03:25.695
What happens next is very simple:

1605
02:03:25.821 --> 02:03:27.155
A single woman,

1606
02:03:27.406 --> 02:03:32.368
childless, who dreams offinally
having her own family.


1607
02:03:32.495 --> 02:03:36.331
She likes the man from across the street,
but he's married.


1608
02:03:36.540 --> 02:03:40.793
She writes him in Chechnya,
telIs him his wife's cheating.


1609
02:03:40.920 --> 02:03:42.921
- Can I see?
- Sure, here.


1610
02:03:43.088 --> 02:03:47.008
And that she's sorry,
but she couldn't keep quiet.


1611
02:03:47.134 --> 02:03:50.803
True or not,
she did write him the letter.


1612
02:03:51.388 --> 02:03:53.139
ltwasjealousy.

1613
02:03:53.307 --> 02:03:56.518
She engineered his divorce.

1614
02:03:56.644 --> 02:03:58.186
Thatwas it!

1615
02:03:58.354 --> 02:04:02.357
No more obstacles.
Just her and him, like the photo.


1616
02:04:02.483 --> 02:04:05.276
All she had to do was
waitfor his return.


1617
02:04:05.486 --> 02:04:08.112
The return of her beloved.

1618
02:04:08.697 --> 02:04:11.282
And he arrives, but not alone.

1619
02:04:11.450 --> 02:04:14.994
He's with a nasty, filthy
savage monkey


1620
02:04:15.120 --> 02:04:17.413
who can hardly speak Russian.

1621
02:04:17.623 --> 02:04:22.752
Remember, she said she asked him
what his plans were?


1622
02:04:23.504 --> 02:04:25.296
And hejust replied

1623
02:04:25.464 --> 02:04:29.551
that he planned to live with the kid
and take care of him.


1624
02:04:29.677 --> 02:04:32.512
Thatwas it. All her hopes, ruined.

1625
02:04:32.763 --> 02:04:34.764
But she kept it up.

1626
02:04:34.932 --> 02:04:38.351
Remember, she said she invited him over.

1627
02:04:38.477 --> 02:04:40.311
With the boy. For her birthday.

1628
02:04:40.479 --> 02:04:44.399
She made dinner, bought sweets,
and a book.


1629
02:04:45.234 --> 02:04:48.444
Later she discovered
that some moneywas missing


1630
02:04:48.571 --> 02:04:52.615
from next to where
that poor boywas sitting.


1631
02:04:53.576 --> 02:04:56.619
And she tried to convince him
to return it.


1632
02:04:57.705 --> 02:05:01.040
Eventually she admitted in court
that she had put it somewhere else


1633
02:05:01.458 --> 02:05:04.919
and forgot.

1634
02:05:05.796 --> 02:05:08.631
But, at the time, she mentions
the money


1635
02:05:08.799 --> 02:05:12.302
in front of a combat vet
who'd been wounded.


1636
02:05:12.428 --> 02:05:15.638
She must have known
what could happen.


1637
02:05:15.764 --> 02:05:17.807
And did happen, of course.

1638
02:05:17.975 --> 02:05:22.270
The man hears that the kid
he considers his son is a thief.


1639
02:05:22.980 --> 02:05:25.023
And he loses control of himself.

1640
02:05:25.649 --> 02:05:28.026
He smacks the boy, but she's silent.

1641
02:05:28.235 --> 02:05:31.613
And when his nose bleeds

1642
02:05:31.739 --> 02:05:34.866
she leaps to his defense
and says the boy's innocent.


1643
02:05:35.034 --> 02:05:38.161
Or rather, he's guilty,
but shouldn't be hit.


1644
02:05:38.287 --> 02:05:41.831
Because children are weaker,
you shouldn't hurt them.


1645
02:05:47.254 --> 02:05:48.838
God!

1646
02:05:50.841 --> 02:05:52.675
She didn't lie.

1647
02:05:52.843 --> 02:05:55.470
She wanted to believe

1648
02:05:55.971 --> 02:05:59.098
the murdererwas the boy

1649
02:06:00.059 --> 02:06:02.101
and no one else.

1650
02:06:03.979 --> 02:06:05.438
Jealousy.

1651
02:06:07.232 --> 02:06:09.317
Senseless, cruel,

1652
02:06:10.319 --> 02:06:13.237
blind, instinctive

1653
02:06:14.782 --> 02:06:16.866
femalejealousy.

1654
02:06:20.329 --> 02:06:22.038
That's it.

1655
02:06:23.248 --> 02:06:24.832
Right there.

1656
02:06:25.501 --> 02:06:28.503
She found the money later,
she said so herself.


1657
02:06:33.258 --> 02:06:34.884
l live with my son.

1658
02:06:35.052 --> 02:06:38.846
He's twenty now, but back then, in"91
he was six.


1659
02:06:39.890 --> 02:06:43.309
ln 1990 mywife left me.

1660
02:06:45.354 --> 02:06:48.940
She ran offwith a guyfrom the States.
The hell with her...


1661
02:06:49.358 --> 02:06:53.903
The kid was upset, of course,
but I explained that momjustwent


1662
02:06:54.988 --> 02:06:58.116
on a long trip, and that
he'd see her again.


1663
02:06:58.242 --> 02:07:01.035
My mom looked after him.

1664
02:07:01.662 --> 02:07:05.331
l had started driving a cab,
working like a dog.


1665
02:07:08.085 --> 02:07:10.878
Didn't really think about myfamily.

1666
02:07:11.255 --> 02:07:14.006
Women are no problem for a cabbie.

1667
02:07:14.174 --> 02:07:15.717
One day...

1668
02:07:16.343 --> 02:07:20.179
...l started talking to this woman.
Not a beauty


1669
02:07:20.556 --> 02:07:24.767
We went out a couple oftimes,
and she came to live with us.


1670
02:07:26.395 --> 02:07:30.314
l didn't need much from her:

1671
02:07:30.441 --> 02:07:33.860
Meals, laundry, take the kid to school.
She seemed to like himjustfine.


1672
02:07:35.028 --> 02:07:36.946
Kolya. Little Nikolai.

1673
02:07:40.033 --> 02:07:43.703
Forthe life of me, I can't remember
how it started.


1674
02:07:49.501 --> 02:07:53.004
She began to tell me things
about my boy...


1675
02:07:53.422 --> 02:07:57.133
...that he was lazy,
that he misbehaved.


1676
02:07:57.259 --> 02:08:00.303
l call him over and ask:
"Is it true?"


1677
02:08:00.471 --> 02:08:05.975
He looks at me, smiling,
and says: "Yes, dad." And hides his eyes.


1678
02:08:06.727 --> 02:08:08.811
l punished him.

1679
02:08:11.690 --> 02:08:16.903
One day I'd had enough,
l don't rememberwhat she told me


1680
02:08:16.987 --> 02:08:20.364
but I just snapped.

1681
02:08:20.491 --> 02:08:22.742
l busted into his room

1682
02:08:22.910 --> 02:08:25.953
dragged him out of bed,
punched him.


1683
02:08:26.121 --> 02:08:29.499
She's quiet.
Then her nose starts bleeding.


1684
02:08:29.625 --> 02:08:31.542
She screams.

1685
02:08:31.710 --> 02:08:36.464
"Murderer! Murderer! What are you doing?!
You're killing the child!"


1686
02:08:37.257 --> 02:08:39.217
And it started.

1687
02:08:39.885 --> 02:08:41.803
I'd beat him...

1688
02:08:43.347 --> 02:08:46.140
She'd see the blood and scream.

1689
02:08:46.308 --> 02:08:48.768
ltwas brutal.

1690
02:08:49.895 --> 02:08:55.024
And my boy, itwas as if
he was expecting it.


1691
02:08:55.108 --> 02:08:58.444
He stopped crying.
He'd just blink and smile,


1692
02:08:58.570 --> 02:09:01.113
blink over and over, but not cry.
He didn't cry.


1693
02:09:01.281 --> 02:09:05.284
l punch him.
His face is bloody.


1694
02:09:05.410 --> 02:09:08.454
And he keeps blinking and smiling.

1695
02:09:09.790 --> 02:09:12.124
Blinking and smiling.

1696
02:09:16.547 --> 02:09:18.673
One night I woke up.

1697
02:09:22.344 --> 02:09:24.679
l heard water running.

1698
02:09:25.180 --> 02:09:28.099
l go to the bathroom,
he's washing his sheet


1699
02:09:28.267 --> 02:09:30.935
He had pissed his bed.

1700
02:09:31.520 --> 02:09:32.979
That kid...

1701
02:09:33.438 --> 02:09:36.357
He sat in the corner
hugging the sheet.


1702
02:09:36.483 --> 02:09:39.402
Looking at me and smiling.
Smiling.


1703
02:09:39.570 --> 02:09:42.363
Blinking and smiling.

1704
02:09:45.534 --> 02:09:48.244
ltwas like he was always guilty.

1705
02:09:48.412 --> 02:09:51.539
That look, and that smile.
He'd look at me...


1706
02:09:51.665 --> 02:09:54.041
And I was right in a way,

1707
02:09:54.209 --> 02:09:56.752
But in my soul, deep down...

1708
02:09:58.630 --> 02:10:02.800
ltwas like someone made me
my own son's executioner.


1709
02:10:03.427 --> 02:10:05.928
Then she had a baby, also a boy.

1710
02:10:06.096 --> 02:10:10.224
He was aboutfour.
He acted up in front of me.


1711
02:10:10.350 --> 02:10:12.643
l gave him a little smack.

1712
02:10:12.811 --> 02:10:16.480
And bam!
God help me...


1713
02:10:16.982 --> 02:10:20.776
l barely got away. She threw an iron,
itjust missed me.


1714
02:10:25.324 --> 02:10:27.491
l could slug my own son,

1715
02:10:27.659 --> 02:10:32.163
but I just barely touched hers,
and she nearly killed me.


1716
02:10:36.460 --> 02:10:40.838
She and the kid went to
her relatives in Tambov.


1717
02:10:45.719 --> 02:10:47.970
l was working nights.

1718
02:10:48.138 --> 02:10:51.974
l had already left the building
when I turned around.


1719
02:10:52.100 --> 02:10:55.978
ltwas like someone grabbed me
by the collar.


1720
02:10:56.104 --> 02:11:00.316
l saw a light in the window.
l ran to the apartment.


1721
02:11:00.609 --> 02:11:03.027
l look all over, can'tfind him.
It's 3am.


1722
02:11:03.195 --> 02:11:05.529
l hear a rustling in the closet.

1723
02:11:05.697 --> 02:11:07.448
l open the closet.

1724
02:11:08.283 --> 02:11:12.828
And he's sitting there.
